||| unique existence. We use subsets and intersections rather than sigmas and
||| pis since the proof of uniqueness is computationally trivial and does not
||| belong in the witness.

Operator unique : (0;1).
[unique(A; B)] =def= [
  prod(A; x. subset(so_apply(B;x); _. isect(A; y. isect(so_apply(B;y); _. =(x;y;A)))))
].

||| unique inhabitation
Operator isContr : (0).
[isContr(A)] =def= [subset(A; x. isect(A; y. =(x; y; A)))].

